%HTTPoison.Response{body: "[{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10915\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10915/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10915/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10915/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/issues/10915\",\"id\":135104813,\"number\":10915,\"title\":\"Hide Typescript generated JS files\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"jaspersorrio\",\"id\":10573718,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/10573718?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/jaspersorrio\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/jaspersorrio\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/jaspersorrio/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/jaspersorrio/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/jaspersorrio/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/jaspersorrio/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/jaspersorrio/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/jaspersorrio/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/jaspersorrio/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/jaspersorrio/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/jaspersorrio/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2016-02-20T17:39:43Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-02-20T17:41:52Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"body\":\"### Description\\r\\n\\r\\nWhen coding in Typescript, the typescript compiler compiles `.ts` files and generates `.js` files.\\r\\n\\r\\nThis causes the tree to be clogged up by the generated `.js` files.\\r\\n<img width=\\\"209\\\" alt=\\\"screen shot 2016-02-21 at 1 29 16 am\\\" src=\\\"https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/10573718/13198090/928ee310-d83a-11e5-9d75-3333e93c5fee.png\\\">\\r\\n\\r\\n### Proposal\\r\\n\\r\\nMake `.ts` file look like a folder and store the generated `.js` files in the folder.\\r\\n\\r\\n### Webstorm's solution\\r\\n<img width=\\\"290\\\" alt=\\\"screen shot 2016-02-21 at 1 36 23 am\\\" src=\\\"https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/10573718/13198120/8eba03c2-d83b-11e5-82fb-6b1b71639b63.png\\\">\\r\\n\\r\\n### atom-typescript issue\\r\\n\\r\\nThis issue is a thorn in the flesh for the typescript community and has been an [issue](https://github.com/TypeStrong/atom-typescript/issues/253) for almost a year.\\r\\n\\r\\n### Steps to Reproduce\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Download apm `apm install atom-typescript`\\r\\n2. Save a `.ts` file.\\r\\n3. Watch your file tree get swamped.\\r\\n\\r\\n### Versions\\r\\n\\r\\nAtom 1.5.3\\r\\napm  1.6.0\\r\\nnpm  2.13.3\\r\\nnode 0.10.40\\r\\npython 2.7.10\\r\\ngit 2.5.4\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10914\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10914/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10914/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10914/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/issues/10914\",\"id\":135093893,\"number\":10914,\"title\":\"Orphan processes\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"alekmych\",\"id\":1730837,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1730837?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/alekmych\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/alekmych\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/alekmych/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/alekmych/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/alekmych/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/alekmych/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/alekmych/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/alekmych/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/alekmych/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/alekmych/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/alekmych/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2016-02-20T16:33:35Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-02-20T16:33:35Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"body\":\"### Description\\r\\n\\r\\nAtom leaves orphan `conhost` and `node` processes under Windows 10 Pro\\r\\n\\r\\n### Steps to Reproduce\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Launch Atom\\r\\n2. Exit Atom\\r\\n\\r\\n**Expected behavior:** Atom clean up correctly without leaving any process\\r\\n\\r\\n**Actual behavior:** Atom leaves `conhost` and `node` processes\\r\\n\\r\\n## Actual process tree\\r\\n### Step 1\\r\\n![step_1](http://i.imgur.com/ygT8Pz7.png)\\r\\n### Step 2\\r\\n![step_2](http://i.imgur.com/2FUEnYO.png)\\r\\n\\r\\n### Versions\\r\\n\\r\\n1.5.3\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10912\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10912/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10912/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10912/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/issues/10912\",\"id\":135016016,\"number\":10912,\"title\":\"Atom.exe command-line output cannot be redirected to a file/pipe\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"FeodorFitsner\",\"id\":5041459,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5041459?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/FeodorFitsner\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/FeodorFitsner\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/FeodorFitsner/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/FeodorFitsner/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/FeodorFitsner/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/FeodorFitsner/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/FeodorFitsner/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/FeodorFitsner/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/FeodorFitsner/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/FeodorFitsner/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/FeodorFitsner/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2016-02-20T01:20:48Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-02-20T01:20:48Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"body\":\"### Description\\r\\n\\r\\nOn Windows atom.exe command-line does not respect redirecting output to a file (or pipe).\\r\\n\\r\\n### Steps to Reproduce\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Open command-line.\\r\\n2. Type `atom.exe -v -w >out.txt`\\r\\n3. Check contents of `out.txt`\\r\\n\\r\\n**Expected behavior:** `out.txt` contains Atom version.\\r\\n\\r\\n**Actual behavior:** `out.txt` is empty and Atom version is printed to the console.\\r\\n\\r\\n### Versions\\r\\n\\r\\n1.5.3\\r\\n\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10910\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10910/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10910/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10910/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/issues/10910\",\"id\":134993375,\"number\":10910,\"title\":\"apm and atom commands not installed by default\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"Nikitaw99\",\"id\":16986290,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/16986290?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Nikitaw99\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/Nikitaw99\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Nikitaw99/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Nikitaw99/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Nikitaw99/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Nikitaw99/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Nikitaw99/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Nikitaw99/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Nikitaw99/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Nikitaw99/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Nikitaw99/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2016-02-19T22:40:43Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-02-19T23:25:14Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"body\":\"### Windows Version:\\r\\n\\r\\nWindows 7 32bit.\\r\\n\\r\\n### Atom Version:\\r\\n\\r\\nLatest (AKA 1.5.3).\\r\\n\\r\\n### Description of the Issue:\\r\\n\\r\\n`apm` and `atom commands` aren't installed by default. The installer I used was **EXACTLY** taken from [atom.io](Https://www.atom.io).\\r\\n\\r\\nBoth the `where apm` and `where atom` commands found nothing.\\r\\n\\r\\nI reinstalled `Atom` a couple of times, and still got the same issue.\\r\\n\\r\\n### [SquirellSetup.log](https://gist.github.com/Nikitaw99/5ec3e454064268bb917d), sorry that half of it is in Russian.\\r\\n\\r\\n\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10909\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10909/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10909/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10909/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/issues/10909\",\"id\":134988401,\"number\":10909,\"title\":\"Add more diagnostics information for better bug reports\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lee-dohm\",\"id\":1038121,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1038121?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lee-dohm\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":true},\"labels\":[{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/enhancement\",\"name\":\"enhancement\",\"color\":\"bfd4f2\"}],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":{\"login\":\"lee-dohm\",\"id\":1038121,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1038121?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lee-dohm\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":true},\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":1,\"created_at\":\"2016-02-19T22:10:42Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-02-19T23:02:07Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"body\":\"### Prerequisites\\r\\n\\r\\n* [X] Can you reproduce the problem in [safe mode](https://atom.io/docs/latest/hacking-atom-debugging#check-if-the-problem-shows-up-in-safe-mode)?\\r\\n* [X] Are you running the [latest version of Atom](https://atom.io/docs/latest/hacking-atom-debugging#update-to-the-latest-version)?\\r\\n* [X] Did you check the [debugging guide](https://atom.io/docs/latest/hacking-atom-debugging)?\\r\\n* [X] Did you check the [FAQs on Discuss](https://discuss.atom.io/c/faq)?\\r\\n* [X] Are you reporting to the [correct repository](https://github.com/atom/atom/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#atom-and-packages)?\\r\\n* [X] Did you [perform a cursory search](https://github.com/issues?q=is%3Aissue+user%3Aatom+-repo%3Aatom%2Felectron) to see if your bug or enhancement is already reported?\\r\\n\\r\\nFor more information on how to write a good [bug report](https://github.com/atom/atom/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#how-do-i-submit-a-good-bug-report) or [enhancement request](https://github.com/atom/atom/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#how-do-i-submit-a-good-enhancement-suggestion), see the `CONTRIBUTING` guide.\\r\\n\\r\\n### Description\\r\\n\\r\\nCreate a \\\"diagnostics API\\\" that will allow `atom --version` and the about-view to display valuable diagnostics information, similar to what is collected by the notifications package for uncaught exceptions.\\r\\n\\r\\n### Steps to Reproduce\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Open a terminal\\r\\n1. Type `atom --version`\\r\\n\\r\\n**Expected behavior:** Diagnostic information including all relevant version numbers, environment variables, etc\\r\\n\\r\\n**Actual behavior:** See below\\r\\n\\r\\n### Versions\\r\\n\\r\\n```\\r\\nAtom    : 1.7.0-dev-b311707\\r\\nElectron: 0.36.7\\r\\nChrome  : 47.0.2526.110\\r\\nNode    : 5.1.1\\r\\n```\\r\\n\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10905\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10905/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10905/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10905/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/issues/10905\",\"id\":134864032,\"number\":10905,\"title\":\"Make non-standard line-endings more visible (stylable)\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"GuillaumeLegendre\",\"id\":561036,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/561036?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeLegendre\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/GuillaumeLegendre\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeLegendre/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeLegendre/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeLegendre/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeLegendre/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeLegendre/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeLegendre/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeLegendre/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeLegendre/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/GuillaumeLegendre/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/enhancement\",\"name\":\"enhancement\",\"color\":\"bfd4f2\"}],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":1,\"created_at\":\"2016-02-19T13:24:51Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-02-19T20:59:48Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"body\":\"Could it be possible to make more visible lines ending who aren't the line ending by default?\\r\\nIn the status bar, on the left of the LF/CRLF/Mixed, I could see a warning icon or the text in red . (yes Mixed would be always with a warning)\\r\\nAnd make in color: red; (or whatever easily seen) and always visible in the file each EOL who aren't the line ending by default.\\r\\n\\r\\nI often receive file with which I have to work from many source. And they aren't always well formed. If Atom could warn me when it happen and where, I could more easily correct it or ask for the sender to correct it by pointing the error.\\r\\n\\r\\nYou can see https://github.com/atom/line-ending-selector/issues/23 my first issue on this matter. With an answer from Lee dohm who is a good start.\\r\\n\\r\\nBut that means having all invisible, visible. Not only the one who are an issue.\\r\\n\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10904\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10904/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10904/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10904/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/issues/10904\",\"id\":134863977,\"number\":10904,\"title\":\"syntax themes: rendering issues with fontsizes > 100%\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"nylki\",\"id\":1710598,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1710598?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/nylki\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/nylki\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/nylki/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/nylki/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/nylki/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/nylki/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/nylki/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/nylki/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/nylki/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/nylki/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/nylki/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/bug\",\"name\":\"bug\",\"color\":\"f7c6c7\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/editor-rendering\",\"name\":\"editor-rendering\",\"color\":\"fef2c0\"}],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2016-02-19T13:24:38Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-02-19T17:16:35Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"body\":\"![ppc_lineissue2](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/1710598/13176596/c362319a-d713-11e5-9896-a94048b5106b.png)\\r\\n\\r\\nDefining a fontsize of more than `100%` for a certain css scope, such as `.heading-1` results in several rendering issues:\\r\\n\\r\\n- Displaced lines, resulting in overlaps.\\r\\n\\r\\n- gutters and cursor height does not match the actual line size / font height\\r\\n\\r\\n- Bigger fontsized lines don't *soft wrap* properly\\r\\n\\r\\nThis is no new issue and it's possibly difficult to prevent, as a lot depends on measuring lines heights etc. and having different sized characters certainly won't make it easier.\\r\\nSome issues, such as a displaced cursor have been fixed previously eg. via https://github.com/atom/atom/pull/8811, but the above ones still exist, that's why I decided opening this issue to collect thoughts and to link connected issues here.\\r\\nIf those issues were nonexistant, some interesting/useful things would be possible in syntax themes.\\r\\n\\r\\nSome discussion has happened here: https://github.com/nylki/pen-paper-coffee-syntax/issues/20\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10903\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10903/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10903/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10903/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/issues/10903\",\"id\":134854947,\"number\":10903,\"title\":\"Splitting/Closing panes results in crash\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"j-moeller\",\"id\":7951928,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7951928?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/j-moeller\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/j-moeller\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/j-moeller/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/j-moeller/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/j-moeller/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/j-moeller/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/j-moeller/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/j-moeller/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/j-moeller/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/j-moeller/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/j-moeller/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/bug\",\"name\":\"bug\",\"color\":\"f7c6c7\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/uncaught-exception\",\"name\":\"uncaught-exception\",\"color\":\"e11d21\"}],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":1,\"created_at\":\"2016-02-19T12:31:21Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-02-19T20:54:53Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"body\":\"### Prerequisites\\r\\n\\r\\n* [X] Can you reproduce the problem in [safe mode](https://atom.io/docs/latest/hacking-atom-debugging#check-if-the-problem-shows-up-in-safe-mode)?\\r\\n* [X] Are you running the [latest version of Atom](https://atom.io/docs/latest/hacking-atom-debugging#update-to-the-latest-version)?\\r\\n* [ ] Did you check the [debugging guide](https://atom.io/docs/latest/hacking-atom-debugging)?\\r\\n* [X] Did you check the [FAQs on Discuss](https://discuss.atom.io/c/faq)?\\r\\n* [?] Are you reporting to the [correct repository](https://github.com/atom/atom/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#atom-and-packages)?\\r\\n* [ ] Did you [perform a cursory search](https://github.com/issues?q=is%3Aissue+user%3Aatom+-repo%3Aatom%2Felectron) to see if your bug or enhancement is already reported?\\r\\n\\r\\n### Description\\r\\n\\r\\n```\\r\\nError:Pane has been destroyed\\r\\n    at Pane.module.exports.Pane.activate (C:\\\\Users\\\\XXXXXX\\\\Atom\\\\resources\\\\app.asar\\\\src\\\\pane.js:631:15)\\r\\n    at Pane.module.exports.Pane.focus (C:\\\\Users\\\\XXXXXX\\\\Atom\\\\resources\\\\app.asar\\\\src\\\\pane.js:207:21)\\r\\n    at atom-pane.<anonymous> (C:\\\\Users\\\\XXXXXX\\\\Atom\\\\resources\\\\app.asar\\\\src\\\\pane-element.js:50:23)\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\n### Steps to Reproduce\\r\\n\\r\\n1. Start with only one pane\\r\\n2. On the pane: Right click > Split Left\\r\\n3. On the right pane: Right click > Split Down\\r\\n4. On the left pane: Right click > Close Pane\\r\\n5. On the upper pane: Right click > Split Down\\r\\n6. On the lower pane: Right click > Close Pane\\r\\n\\r\\n**Expected behavior:** [What you expected to happen]\\r\\n\\r\\n1. After step 5: There are supposed to be three horizontal panes\\r\\n2. After step 6: There are supposed to be two horizontal panes (the two upper ones)\\r\\n\\r\\n**Actual behavior:** [What actually happened]\\r\\n\\r\\n1. After step 5: There are (still) only two panes\\r\\n2. After step 6: The pane is not closed properly (the tab bar remains or the \\\"empty\\\" background is shown)\\r\\n\\r\\n### Version\\r\\n\\r\\n1.5.3 (atom-windows.zip) on Windows 7\\r\\n\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10900\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10900/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10900/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10900/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/issues/10900\",\"id\":134841169,\"number\":10900,\"title\":\"Workspace.scan returned values' structures are different\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"faceair\",\"id\":3659110,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3659110?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/faceair\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/faceair\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/faceair/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/faceair/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/faceair/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/faceair/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/faceair/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/faceair/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/faceair/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/faceair/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/faceair/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/more-information-needed\",\"name\":\"more-information-needed\",\"color\":\"009800\"}],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":3,\"created_at\":\"2016-02-19T11:23:05Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-02-20T02:51:04Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"body\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/blob/master/src/workspace.coffee#L995\\r\\n\\r\\nWhen file is modified, Atom use [TextBuffer.scan](https://atom.io/docs/api/v1.5.3/TextBuffer#instance-scan) replace `directoriesForSearcher`, but `TextBuffer.scan`'s returned value is different with `directoriesForSearcher`.\\r\\n\\r\\nWhat should I do when I used [Workspace.scan](https://atom.io/docs/api/v1.5.3/Workspace#instance-scan) and the returned values' structures are different ?\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10897\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10897/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10897/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10897/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/issues/10897\",\"id\":134737047,\"number\":10897,\"title\":\"Allow panels to have multiple items\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"benogle\",\"id\":69169,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/69169?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/benogle\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/benogle\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/benogle/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/benogle/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/benogle/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/benogle/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/benogle/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/benogle/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/benogle/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/benogle/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/benogle/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":true},\"labels\":[{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/enhancement\",\"name\":\"enhancement\",\"color\":\"bfd4f2\"}],\"state\":\"op