nwduncan\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/nwduncan/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/nwduncan/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/nwduncan/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/nwduncan/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/nwduncan/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/nwduncan/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/nwduncan/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/nwduncan/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/nwduncan/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/needs-reproduction\",\"name\":\"needs-reproduction\",\"color\":\"009800\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/windows\",\"name\":\"windows\",\"color\":\"c7def8\"}],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":8,\"created_at\":\"2016-02-18T01:23:41Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-02-19T04:50:54Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"body\":\"When changing focus from the active atom window to another application's window there is an image/imprint of atom stuck on the screen. Some notes:\\r\\n\\r\\n- If a certain part of the newly active window is refreshed in some way (mouseover a button, panning a map, scrolling, etc.) that section of the window will show through. \\r\\n- Moving the newly active window only removes the atom imprint on sections that leave the view of the screen. \\r\\n- Changing focus via the taskbar does not create this issue. \\r\\n- Minimising atom does not create this issue. \\r\\n- This does not affect all types of windows (ie. Chrome is not affected, but ArcGIS is - seems to only affect Windows GUI based applications). \\r\\n- This issue is also present in safe mode.\\r\\n- Using the most up-to-date version (1.5.3)\\r\\n- This has been present since I installed atom several months ago.\\r\\n\\r\\nRefer to the attached image.\\r\\n\\r\\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/10606760/13130603/6207d07e-d639-11e5-8fdd-eebd2a07f3bc.png)\\r\\n\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10862\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10862/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10862/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10862/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/pull/10862\",\"id\":134299963,\"number\":10862,\"title\":\"Fix for Default Directory Provider incorrectly identifying file paths as URLs on Windows\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"PaulAik\",\"id\":99102,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/99102?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/PaulAik\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/PaulAik\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/PaulAik/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/PaulAik/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/PaulAik/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/PaulAik/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/PaulAik/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/PaulAik/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/PaulAik/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/PaulAik/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/PaulAik/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/atom\",\"name\":\"atom\",\"color\":\"f7c6c7\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/needs-review\",\"name\":\"needs-review\",\"color\":\"bfe5bf\"}],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":7,\"created_at\":\"2016-02-17T14:50:33Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-02-19T20:48:31Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/pulls/10862\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/pull/10862\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/pull/10862.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/pull/10862.patch\"},\"body\":\"Atom's `default-directory-provider` incorrectly identified Windows file paths (e.g. c:\\\\users\\\\paul\\\\text.txt) as URL's. This has a knock-on effect for features such as the Tree View, which shows individually opened files as though they are directories (as opposed to the correct functionality, whereby Tree View shows the file's parent directory and highlights the opened file).\\r\\n\\r\\nThis was because the module was checking for the presence of a protocol in the path passed to it in order to determine whether it was a local file path or a URL (such as atom://config/something). Unfortunately, on Windows the drive letter (e.g. `c:`) was identified as a protocol.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe fix put in place replaces the check for a protocol with one that checks for a hostname. In valid URLs this should come back as a non-empty string, but on Windows it'll come back empty meaning the module correctly identifies the string as a file path.\\r\\n\\r\\nTested on Mac and Windows.\\r\\n\\r\\nLinked tree view issue is [here](https://github.com/atom/tree-view/issues/471)\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10841\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10841/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10841/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10841/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/pull/10841\",\"id\":134037697,\"number\":10841,\"title\":\"Add the -a, --add CLI option\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"ArnaudRinquin\",\"id\":228886,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/228886?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/ArnaudRinquin\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ArnaudRinquin\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/ArnaudRinquin/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/ArnaudRinquin/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/ArnaudRinquin/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/ArnaudRinquin/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/ArnaudRinquin/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/ArnaudRinquin/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/ArnaudRinquin/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/ArnaudRinquin/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/ArnaudRinquin/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/atom\",\"name\":\"atom\",\"color\":\"f7c6c7\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/requires-changes\",\"name\":\"requires-changes\",\"color\":\"fef2c0\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/under-review\",\"name\":\"under-review\",\"color\":\"bfe5bf\"}],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":5,\"created_at\":\"2016-02-16T17:06:15Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-02-19T17:47:12Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/pulls/10841\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/pull/10841\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/pull/10841.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/pull/10841.patch\"},\"body\":\"This commit adds the `-a, --add` option to the CLI which allows users to add paths to the last focused window (similar to Sublime), like shown here:\\r\\n\\r\\n![add-option](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/228886/13084046/9380e642-d4cf-11e5-902a-cd1e126685fd.gif)\\r\\n\\r\\nThis allows you to open many projects in the same Atom window (but not necessarily at the same time) without the hassle of clicking through the menus (right click > Add Project Folder > find my way to the folder...) but doing it from the CLI instead.\\r\\n\\r\\nThis comes with:\\r\\n\\r\\n* a single additional test, I'm not sure if adding more is necessary\\r\\n* documented CLI usage (automated)\\r\\n\\r\\nI'm not sure if that feature needs to be documented elsewhere, if it does I'd be happy to do it.\\r\\n\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10819\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10819/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10819/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10819/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/issues/10819\",\"id\":133615395,\"number\":10819,\"title\":\"Error: Cannot find module '../build/Debug/nodegit.node'\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"mssever\",\"id\":17238705,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/17238705?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/mssever\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/mssever\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/mssever/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/mssever/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/mssever/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/mssever/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/mssever/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/mssever/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/mssever/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/mssever/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/mssever/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/build-error\",\"name\":\"build-error\",\"color\":\"f7c6c7\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/linux\",\"name\":\"linux\",\"color\":\"c7def8\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/more-information-needed\",\"name\":\"more-information-needed\",\"color\":\"009800\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/needs-reproduction\",\"name\":\"needs-reproduction\",\"color\":\"009800\"}],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":7,\"created_at\":\"2016-02-15T03:37:53Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-02-20T13:20:44Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"body\":\"When launching Atom, I get nothing but what appears to be a Chrome JavaScript error page.\\r\\n![atom_057](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/17238705/13039235/2aa28ec8-d362-11e5-8f61-920eb6bbf178.png)\\r\\nThe error in question is:` Cannot find module '../build/Debug/nodegit.node'`.\\r\\n\\r\\nI'm unfamiliar with NodeJS, but it appears to me that perhaps there may be an omission in the [build instructions](https://github.com/atom/atom/blob/master/docs/build-instructions/linux.md). It looks like I'm missing something that I need, but what is it?\\r\\n\\r\\nv.1.6.0beta3 built from source on Ubuntu 14.04 32-bit and installed from a self-built .deb, all done according to the instructions.\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10750\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10750/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10750/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10750/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/issues/10750\",\"id\":132592047,\"number\":10750,\"title\":\"Everything is super slow in hud 4k\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"Oblik-Design\",\"id\":9968597,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/9968597?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Oblik-Design\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/Oblik-Design\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Oblik-Design/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Oblik-Design/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Oblik-Design/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Oblik-Design/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Oblik-Design/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Oblik-Design/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Oblik-Design/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Oblik-Design/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/Oblik-Design/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/performance\",\"name\":\"performance\",\"color\":\"d4c5f9\"}],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":3,\"created_at\":\"2016-02-10T02:27:31Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-02-18T01:46:00Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"body\":\"\\r\\n![capture d ecran 2016-02-09 a 21 29 53](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/9968597/12937216/556211f2-cf74-11e5-8cce-8858379e6b84.png)\\r\\nscrolling, typing . everything is slooow, I mean ridiculous. I've got a monster computer.  \"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10737\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10737/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10737/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10737/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/pull/10737\",\"id\":132342413,\"number\":10737,\"title\":\"Add MRU tab switching functionality\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"natalieogle\",\"id\":11810323,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/11810323?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/natalieogle\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/natalieogle\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/natalieogle/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/natalieogle/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/natalieogle/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/natalieogle/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/natalieogle/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/natalieogle/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/natalieogle/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/natalieogle/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/natalieogle/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/work-in-progress\",\"name\":\"work-in-progress\",\"color\":\"bfe5bf\"}],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2016-02-09T06:29:11Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-02-18T06:03:22Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/pulls/10737\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/pull/10737\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/pull/10737.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/pull/10737.patch\"},\"body\":\"Fixes #5344 \\r\\n\\r\\nFirst thing I did was give the `Pane` class an `itemStack` property to keep track of the order the items were used. The main function I added is `activateNextRecentlyUsedItem` which walks down the `itemStack` each time the user hits tab after ctrl is held down.\\r\\n\\r\\nI set up the keymap for ctrl-tab but I still don't have the keymaps figured out for when ctrl is held down and tab is pressed over and over before lifting up on ctrl.  Something else I need to figure out is how to call a specific function to move an item to the top of the stack once ctrl is lifted.  \\r\\n\\r\\nSo, based on the assumption that I can make a keymap for holding down ctrl and pressing tab over and over (suggestions are welcome), I set up my code so that `activateNextRecentlyUsedItem` would be called each time the user hits tab when holding down ctrl.  Each call to this function would walk down the `itemStack`.  When the user lifted the ctrl key, somehow we would need to call `moveItemToTopOfStack` which would move the item the user stopped on to the top of the stack.\\r\\n\\r\\nI modified the serialization, too, so the `itemStack` would persist.  The 4 scenarios I was focusing on are:\\r\\n- nothing is wrong\\r\\n- no `itemStack` serialized\\r\\n- some items not serialized\\r\\n- for some reason there is a different number of items in the `itemStack` than in the `items` array\\r\\n\\r\\nI wrote tests for the MRU functionality and for the different serialization scenarios.\\r\\n\\r\\nSo yeah, this won't work correctly until I can figure out the key maps for holding ctrl down and hitting tab more than once and until I can figure out how to call `moveItemToTopOfStack` when ctrl is lifted.  \\r\\n\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10732\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10732/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10732/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10732/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/issues/10732\",\"id\":132220687,\"number\":10732,\"title\":\"Alt + menu hotkey doesn't work, closes menu on Windows\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"KeithTurkowski\",\"id\":1822160,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1822160?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/KeithTurkowski\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/KeithTurkowski\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/KeithTurkowski/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/KeithTurkowski/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/KeithTurkowski/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/KeithTurkowski/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/KeithTurkowski/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/KeithTurkowski/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/KeithTurkowski/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/KeithTurkowski/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/KeithTurkowski/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/bug\",\"name\":\"bug\",\"color\":\"f7c6c7\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/windows\",\"name\":\"windows\",\"color\":\"c7def8\"}],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":5,\"created_at\":\"2016-02-08T18:20:54Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-02-19T05:51:52Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"body\":\"When trying to save a file by hitting the key sequence: alt+f alt+s the menu closes and the file does not save.\\r\\n\\r\\nIn every other Windows application I tested, this works. This is done to compensate when typing alt+f s quickly, the release of the alt key does not register before the s key is pressed, or the user does not release it in time.\\r\\n\\r\\nIt is expected that opening the menu, then pressing the hotkey OR alt+hotkey should trigger the action, as this behavior is present in virtually every other Windows application.\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10730\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10730/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10730/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10730/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/issues/10730\",\"id\":132133094,\"number\":10730,\"title\":\"Atom Crash on file actions from networked location (UNC)\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"MadLittleMods\",\"id\":558581,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/558581?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/MadLittleMods\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/MadLittleMods\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/MadLittleMods/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/MadLittleMods/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/MadLittleMods/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/MadLittleMods/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/MadLittleMods/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/MadLittleMods/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/MadLittleMods/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/MadLittleMods/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/MadLittleMods/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":0,\"created_at\":\"2016-02-08T12:46:07Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-02-19T13:45:42Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"body\":\"Atom 1.4.3 with no packages installed on Windows 10.\\r\\n\\r\\nI have [file sharing enabled on a Mac](https://support.apple.com/kb/PH18707?locale=en_US&viewlocale=en_US) and then opening a project on that networked drive in Atom on a Windows 10 machine.\\r\\n\\r\\nVery consistently whenever I do a `npm install` on the mac machine, Atom will crash. I can reproduce it most consistently with `npm install x` or `git checkout x` commands but also happens with file actions like trying to save a new file and mostly doesn't happen when making manual edit. This happens regardless if I have the file open or not. Also happens regardless if the tree view is toggled open.  I have also had it happen when saving a new file in the project on the Windows machine or on the Mac side.\\r\\n\\r\\nWhen the project is open, it shows the UNC path `\\\\\\\\some-mac\\\\Macintosh HD\\\\some-project`\\r\\n\\r\\nNothing appears in the devtools even when looking remotely `--remote-debugging-port=9224` but I am totally open to debugging this further with some instructions.\\r\\n\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10717\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10717/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10717/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10717/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/issues/10717\",\"id\":131840035,\"number\":10717,\"title\":\"\\\"The editor has crashed\\\" - windows 10\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"3nk\",\"id\":5038522,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5038522?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/3nk\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/3nk\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/3nk/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/3nk/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/3nk/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/3nk/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/3nk/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/3nk/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/3nk/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/3nk/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/3nk/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/more-information-needed\",\"name\":\"more-information-needed\",\"color\":\"009800\"}],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":3,\"created_at\":\"2016-02-06T09:57:33Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-02-18T10:40:07Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"body\":\"Hi,\\r\\n\\r\\n\\\"The editor has crashed\\\": This occurs quite often on windows 10 (no specific action or context)\\r\\n\\r\\n![crash](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/5038522/12866051/2a265e6e-ccc0-11e5-9468-9b40f324a186.png)\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10715\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10715/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10715/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10715/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/issues/10715\",\"id\":131838174,\"number\":10715,\"title\":\"UI behaves weird when scrollen / focusing\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"der-Daniel\",\"id\":7686866,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7686866?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/der-Daniel\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/der-Daniel\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/der-Daniel/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/der-Daniel/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/der-Daniel/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/der-Daniel/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/der-Daniel/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/der-Daniel/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/der-Daniel/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/der-Daniel/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/der-Daniel/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/more-information-needed\",\"name\":\"more-information-needed\",\"color\":\"009800\"}],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":4,\"created_at\":\"2016-02-06T09:22:32Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-02-20T00:36:09Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"body\":\"Hi,\\r\\n\\r\\nI am using the latest stable release and when I am scrolling or focusing an element, the UI does things like this:\\r\\n\\r\\n![](http://i.imgur.com/F25PwZ0.png)\\r\\n![](http://i.imgur.com/5z3AQnM.png)\\r\\n![](http://i.imgur.com/uBSp92e.png)\\r\\n\\r\\nI found some similar issues, but none of them fix it for me.\\r\\nThis behavior also appear in safe mode. I do not have any packages installed yet.\\r\\n\\r\\nI am using a DELL XPS 15 with a 3200x1800 resolution.\\r\\nThis high resolution made trouble before.\\r\\n\\r\\nDoes anyone have experienced this before?\\r\\n\\r\\nCheers\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10554\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10554/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10554/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10554/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/issues/10554\",\"id\":128309201,\"number\":10554,\"title\":\"Cursor Disapears after Alt-TAB\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"zoffixznet\",\"id\":5747918,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5747918?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/zoffixznet\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/zoffixznet\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/zoffixznet/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/zoffixznet/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/zoffixznet/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/zoffixznet/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/zoffixznet/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/zoffixznet/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/zoffixznet/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/zoffixznet/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/zoffixznet/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/linux\",\"name\":\"linux\",\"color\":\"c7def8\"}],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":5,\"created_at\":\"2016-01-23T06:29:36Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-02-19T19:20:39Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"body\":\"I'm on Atom 1.4.0 on Bodhi Linux 3.1.1 (fork of Ubuntu 14.04, trusty), running inside VirtualBox on Windows7. I'm having the exact problem described at the start of Issue #3622.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe [screenshot in the third comment](https://github.com/atom/atom/issues/3622#issuecomment-56760573) demonstrates my issue exactly. The [workaround described in a later comment](https://github.com/atom/atom/issues/3622#issuecomment-73421592) did not help (perhaps new Atom has different selectors?).\\r\\n\\r\\nIf I quickly alt-tab back and forth multiple times, I can see the cursor (and the current-line highlight) appears for a few milliseconds, and every about 8 switchings back and forth, the cursor does show correctly.\\r\\n\\r\\nTo note: the cursor just disappears only visibly, but I can still type and I can see the highlight of the line number of the line the cursor is on move when I press Up/Down as well as braces get underlined when I move it horizontally.\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10490\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10490/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10490/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10490/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/issues/10490\",\"id\":127354745,\"number\":10490,\"title\":\"Atom crashes when opening a file from a git repository which has entry contains a forbidden file name on Windows\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"ivellioscolin\",\"id\":6303111,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/6303111?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/ivellioscolin\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/ivellioscolin\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/ivellioscolin/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/ivellioscolin/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/ivellioscolin/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/ivellioscolin/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/ivellioscolin/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/ivellioscolin/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/ivellioscolin/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/ivellioscolin/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/ivellioscolin/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/bug\",\"name\":\"bug\",\"color\":\"f7c6c7\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/git\",\"name\":\"git\",\"color\":\"fef2c0\"}],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":6,\"created_at\":\"2016-01-19T02:51:49Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-02-18T14:24:57Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"body\":\"[Environment]\\r\\nWindows 8.1 64bit\\r\\n\\r\\n[Reproduction Steps]\\r\\n1. Install and run latest atom 1.4.0, no extra package installed.\\r\\n2. Make sure project folder closed in tree view.\\r\\n3. Drag a file from network mapped driver or remote shared folder into atom.\\r\\n\\r\\n[Expected Behavior]\\r\\nFile opened and new project folder created.\\r\\n\\r\\n[Observed Behavior]\\r\\nAtom crashed. (screen shot and crash log attached)\\r\\n[Capture.zip](https://github.com/atom/atom/files/95271/Capture.zip)\\r\\n[Atom Crashes.zip](https://github.com/atom/atom/files/95272/Atom.Crashes.zip)\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n[Installed packages]\\r\\nNo extra package, all built-in Atom packages.\\r\\n\\r\\n[Additional information]\\r\\nIssue can be reproduced in safe mode.\\r\\nIssue has a fail rate to happen, but easy to see when directory depth is deep on network location. I suspect it's related to connection timeout or remote path info. cache not ready.\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10384\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10384/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10384/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10384/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/pull/10384\",\"id\":126094799,\"number\":10384,\"title\":\"Fixed the indentation logic (updated)\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"chfritz\",\"id\":4239098,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/4239098?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/chfritz\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/chfritz\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/chfritz/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/chfritz/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/chfritz/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/chfritz/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/chfritz/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/chfritz/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/chfritz/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/chfritz/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/chfritz/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/atom\",\"name\":\"atom\",\"color\":\"f7c6c7\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/needs-testing\",\"name\":\"needs-testing\",\"color\":\"bfe5bf\"}],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":{\"login\":\"maxbrunsfeld\",\"id\":326587,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/326587?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/maxbrunsfeld\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/maxbrunsfeld\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/maxbrunsfeld/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/maxbrunsfeld/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/maxbrunsfeld/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/maxbrunsfeld/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/maxbrunsfeld/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/maxbrunsfeld/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/maxbrunsfeld/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/maxbrunsfeld/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/maxbrunsfeld/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":true},\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":21,\"created_at\":\"2016-01-12T04:19:59Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-02-19T19:18:06Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"pull_request\":{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/pulls/10384\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/pull/10384\",\"diff_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/pull/10384.diff\",\"patch_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/pull/10384.patch\"},\"body\":\"Previously the logic lacked handling of multiple matches of the\\r\\nincrease/decrease regexs, so things like the following javascript\\r\\nwould not be handled correctly (the last line would be indented).\\r\\n\\r\\n```js\\r\\nif (test) {\\r\\n  foo({a:1\\r\\n  })};\\r\\nvar t = \\\"this should be at indentation 0\\\";\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nFixed that.\\r\\n\\r\\nAlso revisited the logic regarding decreaseIndent and\\r\\ndecreaseNextIndent. It did not seem very logical that decreaseIndent\\r\\ndid *not* correspond to increaseIndent: decreaseIndent regarded the\\r\\ncurrent line whereas increaseIndent regarded the next line (just like\\r\\ndecreaseNextIndent). For that reason I renamed decreaseIndent to\\r\\ndecreaseThisIndent and decreaseNextIndent to decreaseIndent. This way\\r\\nwe also avoid a whole lot of issues related to the concept of\\r\\ndecreaseNextIndent, because most of the language packages I looked at\\r\\nhave not yet adopted it but the semantics of decreaseIndent had\\r\\nchanged. So now the semantics of decreaseIndent is back to what it was\\r\\nand decreaseThisIndent is the new concept.\\r\\n\\r\\nAlso now using the tokenized line to determine whether a in-/decrease\\r\\npattern appears within a quoted string (and ignoring it in that case),\\r\\nrather than requiring regexes for checking whether or not the\\r\\noccurrence is within a quoted string or not -- the examples I saw for\\r\\nthat were wrong, too (e.g., things like `/} [^\\\"] /` are non-sense,\\r\\nbecause things like `} var x = \\\"hey\\\"` are perfectly fine). One really\\r\\nneeds to reason about balanced quotation to get it right, and the\\r\\ntokenizer already does that for us, so let's use it rather than\\r\\nreinventing the wheel. The decrease/increase regexes can now be much\\r\\nsimpler in the language packages.\\r\\n\\r\\nIn this version we use decreaseIndentPattern as the default value for decreaseThisIndentPattern, which is OK, because that pattern is never applied (matched) more than once, which was the previous behavior.\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10309\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10309/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10309/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10309/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/issues/10309\",\"id\":125304960,\"number\":10309,\"title\":\"Problems with accented characters in syntax highlighting?\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"lee-dohm\",\"id\":1038121,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1038121?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/lee-dohm\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/lee-dohm/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":true},\"labels\":[{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/bug\",\"name\":\"bug\",\"color\":\"f7c6c7\"}],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":7,\"created_at\":\"2016-01-07T01:55:39Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-02-19T00:09:55Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"body\":\"It looks like we may have a problem with accented characters with syntax highlighting. We have [a report](https://discuss.atom.io/t/accents-breaks-syntax-highlighting/24263/6?u=leedohm) that describes this as being a problem in:\\r\\n\\r\\n* JS\\r\\n* HTML\\r\\n* PHP\\r\\n* CSS\\r\\n\\r\\nIf this can be verified, we should probably do an audit to ensure that all languages that allow UTF-8 encodings utilize regular expressions that recognize the proper character sets. This especially holds true for text or markup languages like HTML.\\r\\n\\r\\n/cc @atom/languages\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10044\",\"repository_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom\",\"labels_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10044/labels{/name}\",\"comments_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10044/comments\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/issues/10044/events\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/atom/atom/issues/10044\",\"id\":121968959,\"number\":10044,\"title\":\"Quitting and re-opening Atom does not save the same tabs I had open\",\"user\":{\"login\":\"snario\",\"id\":1933029,\"avatar_url\":\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1933029?v=3\",\"gravatar_id\":\"\",\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/snario\",\"html_url\":\"https://github.com/snario\",\"followers_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/snario/followers\",\"following_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/snario/following{/other_user}\",\"gists_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/snario/gists{/gist_id}\",\"starred_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/snario/starred{/owner}{/repo}\",\"subscriptions_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/snario/subscriptions\",\"organizations_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/snario/orgs\",\"repos_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/snario/repos\",\"events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/snario/events{/privacy}\",\"received_events_url\":\"https://api.github.com/users/snario/received_events\",\"type\":\"User\",\"site_admin\":false},\"labels\":[{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/mac\",\"name\":\"mac\",\"color\":\"c7def8\"},{\"url\":\"https://api.github.com/repos/atom/atom/labels/needs-reproduction\",\"name\":\"needs-reproduction\",\"color\":\"009800\"}],\"state\":\"open\",\"locked\":false,\"assignee\":null,\"milestone\":null,\"comments\":20,\"created_at\":\"2015-12-14T03:39:04Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2016-02-20T18:03:51Z\",\"closed_at\":null,\"body\":\"Whenever I quit Atom and re-open it, the same 3 tabs from something I was working on 6 months ago always open and _not_ the thing I was just working on.\\r\\n\\r\\nI have uninstalled and installed the `save-session` package multiple times, no luck.\\r\\n\\r\\nThis is version 1.3.1.\\r\\n\\r\\nI'm guessing some file somewhere has these 3 files of mine saved and this file just never gets updated?\"}]",
